{"title_page": "Jacques Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu", "text_new": "{{Infobox person/Wikidata | fetchwikidata=ALL }}\n\n'''Jacques J\u00e9r\u00f4me Antoine Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu''' (Lorient, 17 November 1747 \u2014 [[Rennes]], 21 June 1829){{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=516}} was a French Navy officer.\n\n== Biography ==\nBorn to the family of a captain of the [[French East India Company]], Trublet joined the Nay in 1780 as a [[capitaine de br\u00fblot]]. During the [[War of American Independence]], he served in the Indian Ocean in [[Suffren]]'s squadron. At the [[Battle of Cuddalore (1783)|Battle of Cuddalore]], he was [[First officer]] on the 56-gun [[French ship Flamand|''Flamand'']], and took command with distinction when her captain, [[\u00c9l\u00e9onor Jacques Marie Stanislas P\u00e9rier de Salvert|P\u00e9rier de Salvert]], was killed. {{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=517}} \n\nAfter the battle, Trublet was promoted to [[Lieutenant (navy)|Lieutenant]] and made a Knight in the [[Order of Saint Louis]]. He remained in the Navy after the [[Peace of Paris (1783)|Peace of Paris]] in 1783. {{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=517}} \n\nBy 1792, Trublet had been promoted to [[Captain (naval)|Captain]]. At the [[Reign of Terror]], he was striped of rank and imprisoned, but survived to retire in Rennes. He never was authorised to rejoin the Navy, but was still restored his rank and pension. There, he published ''Histoire de la Campagne de l'Inde'', an account of the French campaign in the Indian Ocean during the War of American Independence, {{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=517}} where Trublet is very critical of P\u00e9rier de Salvert. {{sfnp|Van Hille||p=20}}\n\nAt the [[Bourbon Restauration]], Trublet recived an honorary promotion to Rear-Admiral. {{sfnp|Levot||p=517}} \n\n== Sources and references ==\n''' Notes'''\n{{Reflist|group=Note}}\n\n'''References'''\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n''' Bibliography'''\n* {{cite book |last1=Cunat |first1=Charles |authorlink1=Charles Cunat|title=Histoire du Bailli de Suffren |date=1852 |publisher=A. Marteville et Lefas |location=Rennes |pages=447 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-jkBAAAAQAAJ}}\n* {{cite book|title=Les gloires maritimes de la France: notices biographiques sur les plus c\u00e9l\u00e8bres marins|last=Levot|first=Prosper|authorlink=Prosper Levot|year=1866|publisher=Bertrand|url=http://books.google.com/?id=08O_XGLO43QC|language=French}}\n* {{cite web |last1=Van Hille |first1=Jean-Marc |title=\u00c9l\u00e9onor Jacques P\u00e9rer de Salvert (1748-1783), Lieutenant de Vaisseau |url=http://www.masoniclib.com/images/images0/955368551466.pdf |accessdate=22 April 2020}}\n\n''' Works '''\n* {{cite book|title=Histoire de la campagne de l'Inde par l'escadre fran\u00e7aise, sous les ordres de M. le bailli de Suffren, ann\u00e9es 1781, 1782, 1783|last1=Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu |first1=Jacques |authorlink1=Jacques Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu|date=An X (1801)|publisher=Veuve Brut\u00e9 |location=Rennes}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Saint-F\u00e9lix, Armand}}\n[[Category:1740 births]]\n[[Category:1819 deaths]]\n[[Category:French Navy officers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox person/Wikidata | fetchwikidata=ALL }}\n\n'''Jacques J\u00e9r\u00f4me Antoine Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu''' (Lorient, 17 November 1747 \u2014 [[Rennes]], 21 June 1829){{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=516}} was a French Navy officer.\n\n== Biography ==\nBorn to the family of a captain of the [[French East India Company]], Trublet joined the Nay in 1780 as a [[capitaine de br\u00fblot]]. During the [[War of American Independence]], he served in the Indian Ocean in [[Suffren]]'s squadron. At the [[Battle of Cuddalore (1783)|Battle of Cuddalore]], he was [[First officer]] on the 56-gun [[French ship Flamand|''Flamand'']], and took command with distinction when her captain, [[\u00c9l\u00e9onor Jacques Marie Stanislas P\u00e9rier de Salvert|P\u00e9rier de Salvert]], was killed. {{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=517}} \n\nAfter the battle, Trublet was promoted to [[Lieutenant (navy)|Lieutenant]] and made a Knight in the [[Order of Saint Louis]]. He remained in the Navy after the [[Peace of Paris (1783)|Peace of Paris]] in 1783. {{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=517}} \n\nBy 1792, Trublet had been promoted to [[Captain (naval)|Captain]]. At the [[Reign of Terror]], he was striped of rank and imprisoned, but survived to retire in Rennes. He never was authorised to rejoin the Navy, but was still restored his rank and pension. There, he published ''Histoire de la Campagne de l'Inde'', an account of the French campaign in the Indian Ocean during the War of American Independence, {{sfnp|Levot|1866|p=517}} where Trublet is very critical of P\u00e9rier de Salvert. {{sfnp|Van Hille||p=20}}\n\nAt the [[Bourbon Restauration]], Trublet recived an honorary promotion to Rear-Admiral. {{sfnp|Levot||p=517}} \n\n== Sources and references ==\n''' Notes'''\n{{Reflist|group=Note}}\n\n'''References'''\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n''' Bibliography'''\n* {{cite book |last1=Cunat |first1=Charles |authorlink1=Charles Cunat|title=Histoire du Bailli de Suffren |date=1852 |publisher=A. Marteville et Lefas |location=Rennes |pages=447 |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-jkBAAAAQAAJ}}\n* {{cite book|title=Les gloires maritimes de la France: notices biographiques sur les plus c\u00e9l\u00e8bres marins|last=Levot|first=Prosper|authorlink=Prosper Levot|year=1866|publisher=Bertrand|url=http://books.google.com/?id=08O_XGLO43QC|language=French}}\n* {{cite web |last1=Van Hille |first1=Jean-Marc |title=\u00c9l\u00e9onor Jacques P\u00e9rer de Salvert (1748-1783), Lieutenant de Vaisseau |url=http://www.masoniclib.com/images/images0/955368551466.pdf |accessdate=22 April 2020}}\n\n''' Works '''\n* {{cite book|title=Histoire de la campagne de l'Inde par l'escadre fran\u00e7aise, sous les ordres de M. le bailli de Suffren, ann\u00e9es 1781, 1782, 1783|Last1=Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu |first1=Jacques |authorlink1=Jacques Trublet de Villej\u00e9gu|date=An X (1801)|publisher=Veuve Brut\u00e9 |location=Rennes}}\n\n{{Authority con